# Databricks Migration Plan

> **Status**: Future goal — local Docker platform first, migrate when stable.
> **Load this file** only when working on infrastructure, paths, secrets, or orchestration.

---

## What Changes (The Big Four)

### 1. Storage Paths
| Current (Docker) | Target (Databricks/Azure) |
|---|---|
| `/opt/spark-data/landing/` | `abfss://medallion@<storage>.dfs.core.windows.net/landing/` |
| `/opt/spark-data/bronze/` | `abfss://medallion@<storage>.dfs.core.windows.net/bronze/` |
| `/opt/spark-data/silver/` | `abfss://medallion@<storage>.dfs.core.windows.net/silver/` |
| `/opt/spark-data/gold/` | `abfss://medallion@<storage>.dfs.core.windows.net/gold/` |

**Migration rule**: Never hardcode paths. Always read from a config object or environment variable so the swap is a one-line change.

### 2. Secrets
| Current (Docker) | Target (Databricks) |
|---|---|
| `.env` file + `os.environ` | Databricks Secrets + `dbutils.secrets.get(scope, key)` |
| `KAFKA_API_KEY` in env | Secret scope: `kafka`, key: `api-key` |
| `KAFKA_API_SECRET` in env | Secret scope: `kafka`, key: `api-secret` |

**Migration rule**: Abstract secret access behind a `get_secret(key)` helper in `src/utils/secrets.py`. Local implementation reads from env; Databricks implementation calls dbutils.

### 3. Table Naming
| Current (2-level) | Target (Unity Catalog, 3-level) |
|---|---|
| `landing.raw_events` | `prod_catalog.landing.raw_events` |
| `bronze.orders_raw` | `prod_catalog.bronze.orders_raw` |
| `silver_base.order_fact_RT` | `prod_catalog.silver_base.order_fact_RT` |
| `silver_enriched.customer_dim` | `prod_catalog.silver_enriched.customer_dim` |
| `gold_curated.fact_orders` | `prod_catalog.gold_curated.fact_orders` |
| `gold_rt.sales_summary_RT` | `prod_catalog.gold_rt.sales_summary_RT` |
| `gold_batch.sales_summary` | `prod_catalog.gold_batch.sales_summary` |

**Migration rule**: All table names must be read from a config dict, never hardcoded inline.

### 4. SparkSession
| Current (Docker) | Target (Databricks) |
|---|---|
| Manual `SparkSession.builder...getOrCreate()` | Removed — Databricks provides `spark` automatically |

**Migration rule**: Wrap SparkSession creation in `src/utils/spark.py` with a `get_spark()` function that detects the environment and returns the appropriate session.

